Policyholders Terms Are Set
Holders who choose to keep their policies with a
newly-created successor company would, by contrast, be
initially credited with about 73 cents on the dollar. Those
policyholders would, for the most part, have to keep their
money with the successor company for five years.
   Executive Life is a unit of First Executive Corp., which
is in Chapter 11 bankruptcy proceedings.
   California insurance regulators have agreed to sell
Executive Life's business to a group of investors led by
Mutuelle Assurance Artisanale de France. Also involved in the
transaction is Altus Finance, which has agreed to buy most of
Executive Life's junk bonds for more than $3 billion. Altus
Finance is a unit of the French bank Credit Lyonnais S.A.